tasks.description:
New file apps/client/src/layers/features/canvas/ui/BlintzCanvas.tsx — a thin controlled wrapper that owns the heavy `blintz` import and its stylesheet, so the editor is isolated to one module (lazy-loadable, single mock point for tests).

Contract:
```
import { MarkdownEditor } from 'blintz';
import 'blintz/styles.css';

export interface BlintzCanvasProps {
  value: string;
  editable: boolean;
  onChange?: (markdown: string) => void;
  className?: string;
}

export function BlintzCanvas({ value, editable, onChange, className }: BlintzCanvasProps) {
  return <MarkdownEditor value={value} editable={editable} onChange={onChange} className={className} />;
}
```
Add module + export TSDoc (the FSD/jsdoc lint rule requires it). This is the DEFAULT export target of React.lazy in CanvasMarkdownContent, so it must `export default` OR CanvasMarkdownContent uses `lazy(() => import('./BlintzCanvas').then(m => ({ default: m.BlintzCanvas })))`. Prefer the named-export + .then(default-map) form to keep a named export for direct test mocking.

Confirm the blintz stylesheet path: blintz package.json `exports` — verify the styles entry (likely 'blintz/styles.css'); if the subpath differs, use the real one (check node_modules/blintz/package.json exports after task 2.0).

Acceptance: file compiles against yalc-linked blintz; no eslint jsdoc errors; not imported anywhere yet except via lazy() in 2.4.
